{
  "number": 1529,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1529",
  "title": "Remove sortBy and use a default sorting scheme",
  "body": "The philosophy of react-instantsearch is now to propose good defaults and provide customisations through connectors.\r\n\r\nWith this in mind, let's implement a default sort for facet widgets: ['isRefined', 'count:desc']. We could further refine this sort by adding a last sort step that would be based on the type of data, strings should be sorted using alphabetical sort and numbers as numbers.\r\n\r\nFinally we should remove the sortBy option from the widget.\r\n\r\nUpdate: 2016-11-15\r\n\r\nThe default will be applied in the connectors, and we'll let the user resort the values if need be.\r\n\r\nConnectors / widgets to update:\r\n - [x] refinementList\r\n - [x] menu\r\n - [x] hierarchicalMenu",
